  "prompt": "What is a recipe like Whole Foods mock chicken salad?",
  "response": "Sure, here's a recipe that closely resembles the Whole Foods mock chicken salad. This vegan salad mimics the taste and texture of chicken salad using plant-based ingredients. \n\n**Ingredients:**\n\n- 1 block (14-16 oz) firm or extra-firm tofu, drained and pressed\n- 1/4 cup vegan mayonnaise\n- 2 tbsp Dijon mustard\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 2 celery stalks, finely diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, finely diced\n- 1/4 cup sweet pickle relish (optional, depending on taste)\n- 1 tsp garlic powder\n- 1 tsp onion powder\n- 1/2 tsp dried dill (or fresh dill to taste)\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Press the Tofu:**\n   - Drain the block of tofu and press out excess water using a tofu press or by wrapping it in paper towels and placing a heavy object on top for about 15-20 minutes.\n\n2. **Prepare the Tofu:**\n   - Once the tofu is pressed, crumble it into small pieces resembling the texture of chicken.\n\n3. **Mix the Dressing:**\n   - In a large mixing bowl, combine the vegan mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, garlic powder, onion powder, dried dill, salt, and black pepper. Mix well until the dressing is smooth and creamy.\n\n4. **Combine Ingredients:**\n   - Add the crumbled tofu to the dressing and mix until the tofu is evenly coated.\n   - Stir in the diced celery, red onion, and pickle relish (if using). Mix all ingredients thoroughly.\n\n5. **Adjust Seasoning:**\n   - Taste the mock chicken salad and adjust the seasoning if necessary, adding more salt, pepper, or lemon juice to suit your taste.\n\n6. **Chill and Serve:**\n   - For best results, refrigerate the salad for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld together.\n   - Serve chilled, either on a bed of greens, in a sandwich, or with crackers.\n\nFeel free to customize the ingredients to your liking, such as adding chopped herbs, nuts, or dried cranberries for extra texture and flavor. Enjoy your mock chicken salad!",
